OL,3,CThe family-run Christmas pudding shop
OL,4,Cwhere business is booming
OL,6,FLily Halpin, 92, still holds special
OL,7,Fmemories of making Christmas puddings
OL,8,Fwith her mother in Ireland.
OL,10,FShe remembers cooking the puddings on
OL,11,Fan open fire.
OL,13,F"That took some doing", she said.
OL,14,F"Especially if the birds knew you were
OL,15,Faround."
OL,17,FEllen Halpin-Barnett, founded the
OL,18,Fbusiness, now known as Nana Lily's, in
OL,19,F2016.
