OL,3,CThe family-run Christmas pudding shop
OL,4,Cwhere business is booming
OL,6,F"As a child we used to make twenty,
OL,7,Fthirty, forty puddings", she recalled.
OL,9,F"It depended who wanted puddings from
OL,10,Fus and we'd give them as gifts. And
OL,11,Fthen a friend of mine said to me the
OL,12,Fone year, we weren't able to make her
OL,13,Fa Christmas pudding, and she had
OL,14,Fbought Christmas pudding and they're
OL,15,Fnot like yours. She said, 'Why don't
OL,16,Fyou do it so that everyone can enjoy?"'
OL,18,FTheir secret recipe has been enjoyed
OL,19,Fby the royal family, and even at the
OL,20,FWhite House. They now sell their
OL,21,Fproduct as far as America and Asia.
